'''Flight Centre Travel Group (FCTG)''' is the largest retail travel outlet in Australia. The company was founded in 1982, and is headquartered in [[Brisbane]], Australia. The company is listed on the [[Australian Stock Exchange]].

FCTG has approximately 2,800 shops and businesses under various retail and corporate brands. It has fully owned operations in Australia, New Zealand, United States, Canada, United Kingdom, South Africa, Hong Kong, India, China, Singapore, United Arab Emirates and Mexico. FCTG has licensee arrangements in a further 80 countries under the corporate brand, FCM Travel Solutions.<ref>http://www.fctgl.com/sites/fctgl.com/files/150918%20FY15%20FLT%20Annual%20Report.pdf</ref>

==Brands==
===United States===
In the United States, [[Liberty Travel]] and GOGO Vacations are the retail and wholesale brands respectively. Specialty corporate brands include [[StudentUniverse]], Worldwide Traveler, Travel Associates, Corporate Traveler, ciEvents, Campus Travel and Stage & Screen.  The North American headquarters is located in Montvale, New Jersey. Other US office locations include New York, Los Angeles, Boston, Philadelphia, Washington DC, Chicago, Atlanta, Miami, Denver, Dallas, Austin, Houston, Phoenix, Seattle, San Francisco, Santa Clara and San Diego.
[[File:Flight Centre, Christchurch, New Zealand.JPG|thumb|right|200px|Flight Centre store in Christchurch, New Zealand.]]

==History==
* 1981,<ref name="financialreviewpipcoates">Pip Coates, 'To Have And To Hold: Geoff Harris. Worth: $975 million. Rank: 40', ''The Australian Financial Review Magazine'', July 2014, p. 22</ref> Co-founded by [[Graham Turner (businessman)|Graham Turner]] and [[Geoff Harris]].
* 1982, the first [[Flight Centre Australia]] store opened in Sydney with assistance from Bill James, who now runs Flight Centre Foundation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kokodatrackfoundation.org/board-of-directors.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-06-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140528030926/http://kokodatrackfoundation.org/board-of-directors.aspx |archivedate=28 May 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.flightcentrelimited.com/our-brands/leisure/flight-centre|title=Flight Centre|work=Flight Centre Limited|accessdate=17 August 2015}}</ref>
* 1995, [[Flight Centre UK]] opened.<ref name="sammartino">André Sammartino (2007), 'Retail’, in Dick, H. & Merrett, D. (eds.), ''The Internationalisation Strategies of Small-Country Firms: The Australian Experience of Globalisation'', Edward Elgar: Cheltenham, UK, pp.175–194.</ref> 
* 1995, [[Flight Centre Canada]] opened.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.fctgl.com/about-us/country-information/canada|title=Canada|work=Flight Centre Travel Group Limited|access-date=2017-05-04|language=en}}</ref> 
* 1999, United States operations recommenced with the company purchasing [[Liberty Travel]] in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.flightcentrelimited.com/our-brands/leisure/liberty-travel|title=Liberty Travel|work=Flight Centre Limited|accessdate=17 August 2015}}</ref>
* 2015, FCTG purchased the US-based StudentUniverse.com<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20151221005748/en/StudentUniverse-Acquired-Flight-Centre-Travel-Group|title=StudentUniverse Acquired By Flight Centre Travel Group {{!}} Business Wire|website=www.businesswire.com|access-date=2017-01-10}}</ref> and Brisbane-based BYOjet.com in December.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fctgl.com/investor-and-media/media-releases/201607|title=Media Releases|access-date=2016-08-01}}</ref>
* 2017, FCTG invested $7 million to take a 24.1 percent stake in Bibam, an Argentinian travel technology company.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://skift.com/2017/04/12/flight-centre-invests-7-million-for-stake-in-leading-argentinian-booking-site/|title=Flight Centre Invests $7 Million for Stake in Leading Argentinian Booking Site}}</ref>

== Awards ==
In 2010, founder Graham Turner was inducted into the [[Queensland Business Leaders Hall of Fame]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://leaders.slq.qld.gov.au/inductees/|title=Hall of Fame|last=|first=|date=|website=[[Queensland Business Leaders Hall of Fame]]|publisher=[[State Library of Queensland]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181023083836/http://leaders.slq.qld.gov.au/inductees/|archive-date=23 October 2018|dead-url=no|access-date=23 October 2018}}</ref>

